Deputy President William Ruto welcomes businessman Jimi Wanjigi at Kasarani as a special guest for the UDA National Delegates Convention. Mr Wanjigi quit ODM last week and joined Safina party. [Courtesy, Twitter]  The United Democratic Alliance party Delegates Convention is currently underway at Kasarani's indoor Arena.  Deputy President William Ruto who is the party leader has so far been nominated as the party's Presidential flag bearer ahead of the August 9 General Election.  Over 5,000 delegates are said to be in attendance.  Deputy President William Ruto is welcome at Kasarani waiting area by Amani National Congress leader Musalia Mudavadi. [Courtesy, Twitter] Amani National Congress leader Musalia Mudavadi shakes hands with Garissa Town MP Aden Duale. [Courtesy, Twitter]  Kapseret MP Oscar Sudi, Senator Milicent Omanga, MP Aisha Jumwa, Governor Anne Waiguru, Senator Susan Kihika and MP Cicily Mbarire among delegates at Kasarani. [Courtesy, Twitter]  Some of the delegates at Kasarani. [Courtesy, Twitter]  Deputy President William Ruto and his wife Rachel at Kasarani. [Elvis Ogina, Standard]  Some of the delegates at UDA's convention at Kasarani. [Elvis Ogina, Standard]  Delegates arrive for UDA national convention at Kasarani. [Elvis Ogina, Standard]  Striking a pose. [Elvis Ogina, Standard]  Â   By Stephanie Wangari | 1 hour ago By Dennis Tarus | 1 hour ago By Stephanie Wangari | 2 hours ago By Patrick Vidija | 2 hours ago